<TEXT>
<P>
In an age of television programming that concentrates on the sensational and 
short interest-span production, it was indeed moving to see "The Fulfillment of 
Mary Gray," a heartfelt story shown on CBS. The acting was superb, as was the 
photography. Most rewarding was the attention paid in great detail to authentic 
dance music of the period, costuming, old-time outdoor picnics and the actual 
use of old farm implements, wagons, cornhusking machines, plows and even an 
antique hat pin holder on the dresser. This attention to detail will stay with 
us forever. 
</P>
<P>
Charles and Sigrid Bausback, La Crescenta 
</P>
</TEXT>
