<TEXT>
<P>
The title of a movie recently shown on KCOP was "Warriors." It dealt with gang 
control of areas, control of gang members by violent leaders, etc. As as 
administrator of a middle school in an area troubled by similar problems, I 
question the motives of the station's programmers. How can my students' parents 
and I convey to our youth that gangs are not OK when this is the offering 
available to them? TV viewing can be educational. Viewing selectively can be 
positive. I think that station programmers have a moral responsibility to 
support positive attributes of our society and oppose those of detrimental 
value. 
</P>
<P>
Linda Brady, Baldwin Park 
</P>
</TEXT>
