Unseasonably balmy weather lingered in the nation's midsection, setting several 
record highs for the day, including a reading of 89 degrees in Amarillo, Tex., 
that shattered the 1972 mark of 83, the National Weather Service reported. 
Lubbock recorded 87 degrees, breaking the 1967 record of 86; Cheyenne, Wyo., 
