<P>
BUILDING BEGUN AT SANTA MONICA CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction has started on the $50-million Lantana Center in Santa Monica, as 
a joint venture of developers Arlene Sellers and Alex Winitsky and Unisys Corp. 
Tishman Realty &amp; Construction Co. is building the five-element campus-style 
office complex designed by architect Arthur Pereira, on a 7.25-acre site at 
3000 W. Olympic Blvd. that formerly served as headquarters for Systems 
Development Corp. 
</P>
