<HEADLINE>
<P>
CS FULLERTON GIVES SNEED 3-YEAR CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton ended its basketball season Friday night with a loss to 
Nevada Las Vegas but applied the finishing touch Saturday by naming John Sneed 
as its basketball coach, giving him a three-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
Sneed, 40, was named acting coach when George McQuarn resigned Nov. 3. He 
guided the Titans to a 16-13 season that included an upset of Nevada Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
Sneed was an assistant under McQuarn for eight years. He was also an assistant 
at Arizona and San Diego State, and had a record of 81-8 in three seasons as 
the head coach at Verbum Dei High School, where his team won the CIF 4-A 
championship in 1974. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
CALIFORNIA STATE UNIVERSITY AT FULLERTON; BASKETBALL; COACHES; CONTRACTS; 
SNEED, JOHN 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
