</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Indonesia's History Through the Ages" will be the subject of a meeting of the 
Asia Society at noon on Wednesday on Level C, Arco Plaza, 505 S. Flower St., 
Los Angeles. Admission free to members, $1 nonmembers. For more information and 
reservations, call (213) 624-0945. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
"Bicycling in Bali" will be the topic of REI, an outdoor gear and clothing 
store, at 6:30 p.m. on Thursday at the store, 3029 E. University Ave., San 
Diego. Admission free. For more information, call (619) 295-7700. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
A slide-lecture on "South America Beyond Expectations" will be presented by the 
Bon Voyage Travel Club at 7:45 p.m. on Friday in the Community Room, 9696 
Wilshire Blvd., Beverly Hills. Admission $5. For more information, call (213) 
472-5726. 
</P>
<P>
 -- -- -- 
</P>
<P>
A seminar on "Work Your Way Around the World" will be held by American Youth 
Hostels, Los Angeles Council, at 1 p.m. on Saturday at the AYH Travel Center, 
335 West 7th St., San Pedro. Admission $10. Pre-registration is suggested. For 
more information, call (213) 831-8846 or (213) 831-8847. 
</P>
