<HEADLINE>
<P>
JUST RELEASED IN PAPER: FICTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THE TENANTS OF TIME by Thomas Flanagan (Warner: $5.95). Three men, during the 
1800s, participate in a failed Irish revolt that affects them throughout their 
lives. 
</P>
<P>
BLACK HEARTS AND SLOW DANCING by Earl W. Emerson (Penguin: $3.95). Mac Fontana 
doggedly pursues the murderer of a firefighter in his temporary role as sheriff 
in Staircase, Wash. 
</P>
<P>
THE LAST PRINCESS by Cynthia Freeman (Berkley: $4.95). On her wedding day, a 
woman jilts her fabulously wealthy fiance to marry a penniless, ambitious man. 
</P>
<P>
STORIES by Elizabeth Jolley (King Penguin: $7.95). Combination of two of 
Jolley's successful short-story collections about the vicissitudes of life. 
</P>
<P>
ROYAL BLUE by James Reardon (St. Martin: $4.50). Jimmy Riley's badge opened a 
lot of doors for him, but it imprisoned him when repayments became due. 
</P>
<P>
NONFICTION 
</P>
<P>
THE PRIZE PULITZER by Roxanne Pulitzer with Kathleen Maxa (Ballantine: $4.95). 
Pulitzer contends that the sobriquet "strumpet with the trumpet" is undeserved. 
</P>
<P>
SEASON TICKET: A Baseball Companion by Roger Angell (Ballantine: $4.95). 
Angell, a baseball connoisseur, writes on the finer points of the game -- the 
craft and techniques, over a five-year period. 
</P>
<P>
CELLAR OF HORROR by Ken Englade (St. Martin's: $4.50). Gary Heidnik, a mentally 
disturbed self-proclaimed minister, chained, starved, sexually assaulted and 
mutilated women in a Philadelphia neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
DANGEROUS DOSSIERS: Exposing the Secret War Against America's Greatest Authors 
by Herbert Mitgang (Ballantine: $4.95). Utilizing the discovery powers of the 
Freedom Information Act, Mitgang exposes the diatribes against artists 
maintained by the FBI in secret dossiers. 
</P>
<P>
TIME IS ALL WE HAVE: Four Weeks at the Betty Ford Center by Barnaby Conrad 
(Dell: $4.95). A personal account of the drug and treatment facility frequented 
by the rich and famous. 
</P>
<P>
SELF-HELP / REFERENCE 
</P>
<P>
READING THE NUMBERS by Mary Blocksma (Penguin: $7.95). Did you ever look at 
your purchases and wonder what those stripe markings, ISBN numbers or Social 
Security numbers reveal? These and more are explained. 
</P>
<P>
SCULPTURE: A Man's Guide to Cosmetic Surgery by Mark A. Mandel MD (Paperjacks: 
$4.50). Plastic surgeon coaches men on the procedures, risks, costs and results 
of hair transplants, wrinkle removal, liposuction and face lifts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Book Review 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031289-0214 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 30111 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 12, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
