<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEATHER FORECAST: IT'S IN THE (TIMES) BAG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re meteorology-Orange County: I am bemused by the weather antics on television 
of Doctor George, Willard Scott, et al., as they are almost invariably "wrong." 
</P>
<P>
For the 20 years I have lived in Anaheim, Orange, Irvine and Newport Beach, I 
have found a far more reliable forecaster of weather: my Los Angeles Times 
delivery person! 
</P>
<P>
If, when I walk out to the driveway to retrieve my Times, it is in a plastic 
cover, I know we will have rain in the near future -- and dress accordingly. 
</P>
<P>
If the good doctor and Willard forecast rain, and my Times is unwrapped, I 
dress for a fine and clear day. 
</P>
<P>
It works. Try it! 
</P>
<P>
WARREN ISHAM 
</P>
<P>
Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
