<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER KILLS BOY IN ALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 7-year-old boy died after he was struck by a speeding hit-and-run driver 
Saturday in an alley off Jeffrey Drive in an apartment complex near the 
Disneyland Hotel, Anaheim police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were searching late Saturday for a cream-colored sedan with a damaged 
left front fender. Witnesses told police the driver never stopped after the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Hit Garage Doors 
</P>
<P>
The car entered the alley near the 1600 block of Jeffrey Drive at a high rate 
of speed and hit several garage doors before striking Victor Martinez Magana of 
Anaheim. Magana was taken to Western Medical Center-Anaheim where he died an 
hour later of massive head and chest injuries, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police were not sure what the boy was doing in the alley. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said witnesses saw the car but none of them saw the vehicle strike the 
child. Officials were not sure where the boy was standing when he was hit. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim Police Sgt. Fred Roush said the child lived in the area of the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
Several hours earlier, Anaheim police reported that a father accidently ran 
over his 2-year-old child in the area of Bywood Avenue. The child was rushed to 
Anaheim Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital spokesperson reported Saturday night that the child was in stable 
condition with foot injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Details of the accident and the names of the child and father were not 
available, police said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TRAFFIC ACCIDENTS -- ORANGE COUNTY; HIT AND RUN DRIVERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
